@LlmRouter_HostAddress = https://localhost:7225
@Model = gemini-2.5-flash

# Chat body quick reference:
# - model: logical model name. The router uses it to find compatible providers.
# - messages: provider-neutral conversation history.
# - role: usually user, assistant, or system.
# - content: text sent to the LLM.
# - maxTokens: optional completion token limit.
# - temperature: optional randomness value between 0 and 2.
# - strategy: LeastLatency, RoundRobin, or PriorityWithFallback.
### Built-in health check
GET {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/health

### Provider health snapshots
GET {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/health/providers
Accept: application/json

### OpenAPI document
GET {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/openapi/v1.json
Accept: application/json

### Chat smoke test - Gemini
POST {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/v1/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "model": "{{Model}}",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Explain in three concise bullets what problem a multi-provider LLM router solves."
    }
  ],
  "maxTokens": 200,
  "temperature": 0.2,
  "strategy": "PriorityWithFallback"
}

### Validation failure example
POST {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/v1/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "model": "{{Model}}",
  "messages": [],
  "maxTokens": 200
}

### Unsupported model example
POST {{LlmRouter_HostAddress}}/v1/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "model": "unsupported-model",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hello"
    }
  ]
}

